 FROM SACARAP' TO PORTLAND PIER
 I'VE CARTED STONE THIS MANY A YEAR;
 TILL, KILLED BY BLOWS AND SORE ABUSE,
 THEY SALTED ME DOWN FOR SAILORS' USE.
 THE SAILORS THEY DO ME DESPISE;
